Author: Zhang, ShengWen
RenLiu,
Jiang, JinQiang
Yang, Cheng

CommonFields.Location: School of Chemical & Material Engineering, Jiang Nan University, Wu Xi 214122, PR China

ChooseParameter.Other: polyethylene glycol was distilled at 100 C for 2 hrs before use

Drying-Evaporation.Description: Dimethylol propionic acid (DMPA) was dried in a vacuum oven before use

ChooseParameter.Other: Hydroxyethyl methacrylate (HEMA) was also distilled before use.

Drying-Evaporation.Description: Acetone was dried over 4A molecular sieves before use

ChooseParameter.Other: Isophorone diisocyanate (IPDI) was charged into a 250 ml dried 4-necked flask equipped with a mechanical stirrer, thermometer, condenser, and nitrogen in/outlet.
31.5 g polyethylene glycol (PEG) 400 and 4 drops of dibutyltin dilaurate (DBTDL) were added dropwise
The mixture then reacted at 45 ◦C for 1–2 h
During the reaction isocyanate (NCO) content was monitored using the standard dibutylamine back-titration method
When theoretical value of NCO value was reached 2.85 g hydrophilic monomer (DMPA) and 2 drops of DBTDL were added
This mixture reacted at 60 ◦C until another theoretical value was reached.
2.6 g Hydroxyethyl methacrylate (HEMA) and 0.6 g of the inhibitor hydroquinone were added to react at 70 ◦C for 3–4 h
Acetone was added during the process to adjust the viscosity of the PU prepolymers

Mixing.Description: TEA was added to neutralize the resulting resulting PU prepolymers

Filler.Description: The filler used was an aqueous silica sol

Mixing.Description: The aqueous silica sol was then added to the mixture and stirred.

ChooseParameter.Other: Water was slowly added to neutralized acetone solution of PU prepolymers at ambient temp. with an agitations speed of 600 rpm

Drying-Evaporation.Description: The dispersion was then transferred to a rotary evaporator to remove acetone

Mixing.Description: 3–4 wt% of photoinitiator (Irgacure 2959) was added and dispersed into previous dispersion.

MoldingInfo.Description: Films were prepared by casting onto a Teflon mold.

ChooseParameter.Other: Films were irradiated from one side using 200W UV (365 nm) lamp for 2 min at rt

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Equipment: TA Instruments DMA 2980 dynamic mechanical analyzer

Atomic_Force_Microscopy.Description: The scans were performed in tapping mode

Rheometery.Description: Used modes of steady shear flow and dynamic oscillatory shear at 25 C
Rheometery.Equipment: Advanced Rheometric Expansion System (ARES, Rheometric Scientific Instruments, USA)

OpticalMicroscopy.Equipment: ZS90 Zetasizer nano-zeta potential analyzer (Malvern, UK)
